### Accessibility

Spectrum components are **accessible by default**, but follow these practices:

```typescript
// ✅ Always provide labels
<TextField label="Email" />

// ✅ Use aria-label for icon-only buttons
<Button aria-label="Delete item">
  <Delete />
</Button>

// ✅ Provide meaningful descriptions
<TextField
  label="Password"
  description="Must be at least 8 characters"
  errorMessage="Password is too short"
/>
```

### Responsive Design

```typescript
import { useBreakpoint } from '@adobe/react-spectrum';

function MyComponent() {
  const breakpoint = useBreakpoint();
  
  return (
    <Flex direction={breakpoint === 'S' ? 'column' : 'row'}>
      {/* Responsive layout */}
    </Flex>
  );
}
```

### State Management

```typescript
// ✅ Controlled components
const [value, setValue] = useState('');

<TextField
  label="Name"
  value={value}
  onChange={setValue}
/>

// ✅ Form validation
const [isValid, setIsValid] = useState(true);

<TextField
  label="Email"
  validationState={isValid ? 'valid' : 'invalid'}
  errorMessage={!isValid && "Please enter a valid email"}
/>
```

### Common Patterns

#### Loading States
```typescript
import { ProgressCircle, Button } from '@adobe/react-spectrum';

{loading ? (
  <ProgressCircle aria-label="Loading" isIndeterminate />
) : (
  <Button>Submit</Button>
)}
```

#### Empty States
```typescript
import { IllustratedMessage, Heading, Content } from '@adobe/react-spectrum';
import NotFound from '@spectrum-icons/illustrations/NotFound';

<IllustratedMessage>
  <NotFound />
  <Heading>No results found</Heading>
  <Content>Try adjusting your search criteria</Content>
</IllustratedMessage>
```

#### Toast Notifications
```typescript
import { ToastContainer, useToast } from '@adobe/react-spectrum';

function MyComponent() {
  const toast = useToast();
  
  const showToast = () => {
    toast.positive('Operation successful!', { timeout: 3000 });
  };
  
  return (
    <>
      <Button onPress={showToast}>Show Toast</Button>
      <ToastContainer />
    </>
  );
}
```

### Theme Customization

```typescript
import { Provider, theme } from '@adobe/react-spectrum';

// Use custom theme
<Provider theme={theme} colorScheme="dark">
  {/* Your app */}
</Provider>

// Or default theme
<Provider theme={defaultTheme}>
  {/* Your app */}
</Provider>
```

### Performance Tips

1. **Use memoization for expensive renders:**
```typescript
const MemoizedCard = memo(ODPCard);
```

2. **Use collections efficiently:**
```typescript
import { ListView, Item } from '@adobe/react-spectrum';

<ListView items={odps}>
  {(item) => <Item key={item.id}>{item.name}</Item>}
</ListView>
```

3. **Avoid unnecessary re-renders:**
```typescript
const handleChange = useCallback((value: string) => {
  setValue(value);
}, []);
```

### Common Mistakes to Avoid

**DON'T**:
```typescript
// ❌ Don't mix UI frameworks
import { Button } from '@mui/material'; // NO!

// ❌ Don't use pixel values
<View padding="16px"> // Use size tokens!

// ❌ Don't forget Provider
<Button>Click me</Button> // Won't work without Provider

// ❌ Don't use div/span for layout
<div style={{ display: 'flex' }}> // Use Flex component!
```

**DO**:
```typescript
// ✅ Use Spectrum exclusively
import { Button } from '@adobe/react-spectrum';

// ✅ Use size tokens
<View padding="size-200">

// ✅ Wrap in Provider
<Provider theme={defaultTheme}>
  <Button>Click me</Button>
</Provider>

// ✅ Use Spectrum layout components
<Flex direction="row" gap="size-200">
```

### When to Use MCPs (Live Data)

Prefer **MCP tools** for live component APIs, tokens, icons, and docs so the rule stays focused on conventions.

| Need | MCP Server | Tools |
|------|------------|--------|
| Component API, props, examples | **React Spectrum S2** | `list_s2_pages` → `get_s2_page_info` → `get_s2_page` (by `page_name`, optional `section_name`) |
| Size/color token allowed values | **React Spectrum S2** | `get_style_macro_property_values` (e.g. `propertyName`: `"padding"`, `"gap"`) |
| Icon or illustration by term | **React Spectrum S2** | `search_s2_icons`, `search_s2_illustrations` (`terms`: string or string[]) |
| Color/pixel → closest token | **Spectrum Vars MCP Server** | `search_spectrum_vars` (`query`: color or pixel, `scale`: MEDIUM/LARGE) |
| Latest docs or code examples | **context7** | `resolve-library-id` (e.g. "React Spectrum") → `query-docs` with specific question |

Use this rule for: Provider requirement, sizing principle (tokens not pixels), Spectrum-only policy, and patterns. Use MCPs when you need current API details, token value lists, or icon/illustration names.

